Here is the requested detailed breakdown of the information provided in the Executive Document Summary form in JSON format:

```json
{
  "header": "INDIANA DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION SECTION 5310 CAPITAL GRANT AGREEMENT",
  "grantee": "Blue River Services Inc",
  "eds_number": "EDS #A249-21-G200126",
  "document_content": [
    "This Grant Agreement ('Grant Agreement'), entered into by and between the State of Indiana, acting through its Department of Transportation, Office of Transit (the 'State') and Blue River Services Inc (the 'Grantee'), jointly referred to as the 'Parties,' is executed pursuant to the terms and conditions set forth herein.",
    "Whereas, 49 U.S.C. §5310 authorizes the Federal Transit Administration ('FTA'), to make grants to states to be used for transportation projects to provide transportation services for the elderly and individuals with disabilities ('Section 5310 Capital Grant'); and",
    "Whereas, the Indiana Department of Transportation ('INDOT') is authorized by IC §8-23-2-4.1(2)(C) to select projects for approval by the FTA and to administer Section 5310 Capital Grants; and",
    "Whereas, the Grantee, a private nonprofit organization, has been awarded a Section 5310 Capital Grant by INDOT and the FTA, and is a 'subrecipient' as that term is defined in 49 U.S.C. §5310;",
    "Now, therefore, in consideration of the mutual covenants set forth herein, the State and the Grantee agree as follows:"
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "1. Purpose of this Grant Agreement": [
        "The purpose of this Grant Agreement is to memorialize the terms, conditions and mutual understandings pursuant to which the Grantee will utilize a Section 5310 Capital Grant of up to $72,964.80 ('Grant funds') to provide transportation services to the elderly and/or disabled as set forth in the project ('the Project') described in Exhibit A, attached hereto and incorporated fully herein."
      ]
    },
    {
      "funding_source": {
        "if_federal_funds": "Program Name per Catalog of Federal Domestic Assistance ('CFDA'):",
        "checked_box": "Enhanced Mobility of Seniors and Individuals with Disabilities – Section 5310 Program",
        "cfda_number": "20.513"
      }
    },
    {
      "2. Term": [
        "This Grant Agreement shall be effective for a period of four (4) years. It shall commence from the date of the last state signatory."
      ]
    },
    {
      "3. Audits, Maintenance of Records, and Reports": [
        {
          "A": [
            "Unless a written waiver has been obtained from the State Board of Accounts, the Grantee shall hire an independent auditor to conduct an annual audit of the Project in accordance with 2 CFR 200 'Uniform Administrative Requirements, Cost Principles, and Audit Requirements for Federal Awards.'"
          ]
        },
        {
          "B": [
            "If the Grantee is a non-governmental unit, the Grantee shall file the Form E-1 annual financial report required by IC §5-11-1-4. The E-1 entity annual financial report will be used to determine audit requirements applicable to non-governmental units under IC §5-11-1-9. Audits required under this section must comply with the State Board of Accounts Uniform Compliance Guidelines for Examination of Entities Receiving Financial Assistance from Governmental Sources."
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

This JSON structure captures the details from the provided document, including the header, the grantee information, the EDS number, the main content paragraphs, and specific sections of the agreement. For checkboxes, the value of the checked box is provided.
